# Analytics Guidelines

## Overview
For related guidelines:
- Error Handling: See `error-handling.mdc`
- State Analytics: See `state-management.mdc`
- Testing Analytics: See `testing.mdc`

## Required Events

### Lifecycle Events
- Feature initialization
- Feature disposal
- Screen views
- Modal/dialog displays

### User Interaction Events
- Button clicks
- Form submissions
- List item selections
- Navigation actions
- Search queries

### Operation Events
- Operation start
- Operation success
- Operation failure
- Operation cancellation

## Event Properties
- Timestamp
- User context
- Feature context
- Action context
- Error details (if applicable)
- Performance metrics

## Implementation

### Analytics Interface
```dart
abstract interface class IFeatureAnalytics {
  void logInitialized();
  void logActionStarted();
  void logSuccess();
  void logFailure(Object error);
}
```

### Best Practices
- Track all user interactions
- Include relevant context
- Log error details
- Track performance metrics
- Use consistent event naming
- Group related events
- Avoid sensitive data
- Implement proper error handling

## Error Tracking
- Log all error states
- Include error type
- Include error message
- Track stack traces
- Log user actions leading to error
- Track error recovery attempts

## Performance Tracking
- Track operation duration
- Monitor resource usage
- Track UI rendering time
- Log network request times
- Monitor memory usage

## Data Privacy
- No PII in analytics
- No sensitive data
- Follow GDPR guidelines
- Implement data retention
- Allow analytics opt-out 